channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Devastation in Gaza as Israel wages war on Hamas
item.description: At least 40 people were killed in an Israeli airstrike on a UN-run school in the Nuseirat refugee camp in central Gaza overnight, Palestinian authorities said Thursday. Follow for live updates.

item.title: The last heroes of Normandy return to France 80 years after D-Day invasion
item.description: On the 80th anniversary of D-Day, "World News Tonight" anchor David Muir reports on the last heroes of Normandy as they return with a message for the next generation.

item.title: Rare juvenile T. rex fossil found by children in North Dakota to go on display
item.description: The "Teen Rex" is one of just four young T. rex fossils that have been found on Earth.

item.title: Day 4 of Hunter Biden's federal gun trial
item.description: Day four of Hunter Biden's trial on gun charges in Delaware featured testimony from Hallie Biden. The president's son faces three charges in the case brought by a special counsel.

item.title: NBA Commissioner Adam Silver says finalizing the new media rights deals is 'complex' process
item.description: Getting the NBA’s next round of media rights deals completed is an extremely complex proposition, Commissioner Adam Silver said Thursday, especially because nobody can say with any certainty what the viewing landscape will look like in the future

item.title: Who will be Trump's 2024 VP pick? These are the contenders
item.description: CBS News has learned that multiple potential 2024 running mates for former President Donald Trump, the presumptive Republican presidential nominee, have received vetting documents. The search is set to end ahead of July's Republican National Convention. Political strategists Ashley Etienne and Hogan Gidley join "America Decides" to take a look at the contenders.

item.title: 'The day has finally come': Years in the making, evidence leads investigators to Rex Heuermann
item.description: Rex Heuermann left his office near the Empire State Building and strolled down a still-bustling Fifth Avenue as the sun set on a hot Thursday evening in Manhattan.

item.title: What we know about the women known as the 'Gilgo Four'
item.description: Of the six women Rex Heuermann is accused of killing on Long Island, four of them were discovered bound with belts or tape and wrapped in burlap along a stretch of Gilgo Beach in 2010.

item.title: Hallie Biden, widow of Beau, testifies in Hunter Biden's gun trial
item.description: Hunter Biden's ex-girlfriend Hallie Biden, who is also the widow of his brother Beau, delivered emotional testimony Thursday in Biden's federal gun trial. She talked about how she discovered the weapon in his truck in October 2018 and then "panicked" and threw it away at a Delaware grocery store parking lot, because she "didn't want him to hurt himself or the kids to find it and hurt themselves." Scott MacFarlane has details.
